        11 September 2020 - 17 September 2020

        The Official Singles Chart Top 100 reflects the UKs biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1. View the biggest songs of 2025.

        Replying to each point...

        (Negative)

        1) I could see this going up for the next couple of weeks, due to Ava's new album being released this coming Friday.

        2) 'Exile' shouldn't fall as far on the next chart, but my love for EDM just outshined my love for 'Folklore' this week apparently.

        3) 'Dancing In The Moonlight' lost a lot of radio airplay everywhere this week, so that caused me to listen to it less too!

        (Mixed)

        1) Only Megan's verses are keeping it afloat this week, along with the clean edit picking up a lot of radio support now, but it probably won't last any longer!

        2) A lot of foreign language songs tend to do this for me! They'll stay on repeat for a few days, then they'll end up just getting mostly forgotten. The trend didn't change this with song among the Dutch ones!

        (Positive)

        1) It probably won't spend any more weeks at #1, but at least you got to see this song become my longest EDM leader of all-time!

        2) Both of these are going to climb next week, even if topping the charts is a bit beyond reach for either of them.

        3) I don't know what happened this week, but I'm obsessed with it now! It's looking like it'll go all the way next time.

        4) 'You Broke Me First' being the biggest climber of the week shows you how much I've really warmed to it! The same is happening to 'Midnight Sky' at the moment & 'Greece' to a less extent. While I don't really like TikTok as an app, a remix of 'Love Story' is getting popular on it, hence the big move up my charts!

        5) The song as a whole is decent, but that final minute is so relaxing! I needed that this week, hence why it's back.

        WEEKLY CHART REVIEW (11/09/2020 - 17/09/2020)

        (Negative)

        1) Im honestly still not enjoying Wap at #1! The production nor Cardis verses have grown on me, plus the content is still incredibly unsettling.

        2) ACR in general! Seriously, Im just grouping this together because it killed off so many awesome EDM summer anthems like Head & Heart, Heaven On My Mind & Dancing In The Moonlight, West Ten, 'Secrets' & 'Kings & Queens', to name just a few. I decided to put this as one point, because making four separate negatives would just be even more depressing!

        3) Take You Dying (oh, sorry, Take You Dancing), climbed again this week! It mightve just fallen short of the Top 10 today, but given how long its got until ACR, I have the sinking feeling that itll get there very soon.

        4) Oh no, Popstar is back! Lets be honest, who even cares about this song?! Its only back in the chart because everyone went wild for the official video as it featured Justin Bieber. Ill just stick with Greece, thank you very much!

        5) 'Lemonade' is actually that forgettable that I had to edit my review to include it here! I would say that's actually funny, if the song didn't (which, for the record, it does!).

        (Mixed)

        1) Mood Swings reached the Top 5! I dont like the lyrics at all, but the vocals & production are chill to make this Pop Smokes best song yet.

        2) Despite it being a much older song, I actually dont mind Watermelon Sugar falling (as Harry would say) this week, because its getting so overplayed that radio had to give it a break at some point.

        3) I am warming to Heather a little bit, but its still not connecting with me in the same way that it is for others. Im finally starting to see the appeal behind it though!

        4) 'Tap In', 'Dance Monkey' & 'Cardigan' all moved up, but not enough to make a re-appearance in the Top 40.

        5) The Rolling Stones set a new record on the albums chart, although I've heard absolutely nothing from it yet, haha.

        (Positive)

        1) Mood climbed to the runner-up spot! It looks like this is now a hit about everywhere which is awesome, but it continuing that TikTok momentum allowing to become the next #1 single would be the icing on the cake.

        2) Aint It Different took advantage of the clearout week & hit a new peak! All three artists go hard on this, which you dont really see often in a UK rap collaboration nowadays.

        3) Looking For Me finally broke the Top 10! Yeah, the song is basic, but thats what makes it so immediately catchy. Also, that beat is incredible, even without the bass being boosted! Honestly, this would fit clubs perfectly if they were open right now.

        4) Im so happy that we can add Miley Cyrus to the list of mainstream artists who are bringing back the throwback disco vibe in 2020. This also going Top 10 is amazing, but I think it has the potential to be even bigger in the coming weeks, given how well its selling!

        5) You Broke Me First is still gathering attention fast! Tate McRae deserves it though & if she keeps making music in this lane, I could honestly see her sticking around for a while! This has to go Top 10 next week, surely?

        6) Tick Tock might be getting attention a little slower, but its certainly moving in the right direction & more importantly, its consistent across all chart metrics!

        7) How did 'Blinding Lights' rebound again?! Is it even on ACR yet, or are people just loving it so much that they decided to give it another push? Either way, I'm certainly not complaining, especially when it's such a modern masterpiece!

        8) How did I miss out mentioning that 'Giants' took an insane boost thanks to Dermot Kennedy's Soccer Aid appearance & Radio 1 overplaying it, haha! Either way, I'm so glad this song is finally here. It really took a while (probably even longer than 'Outnumbered'), but better late than never!

        9) 'Lasting Lover' sounds really good on first listen! James Arthur sounds a lot more interesting over this production & Sigala's immediately addictive drops never disappoint me.

        10) Bring Me The Horizon somehow got another Top 40 hit in 2020! Its honestly so exciting to see a metal group back in the singles chart, especially when theyre bringing this much energy from the entire group & raw vocal presence. Im glad YUNGBLUD is here too, he fits in better than I expected!

        11) Both Come & Go & Hallucinate rebounded, which pleasantly surprised me, given that I thought both of them would be out by now.

        Thanks for reading everybody! ;)
